<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 31 at 12:51AM EST  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...Areas of Fog to Continue Through This Morning...
Areas of fog and low clouds remain across portions of northern
Ohio and Northwest Pennsylvania this morning. Visibility will
average around one mile across the region but pockets of dense fog
of one quarter of a mile or less are possible. Fog will then
begin to lift in the morning and travel conditions will improve.
Motorists may encounter fluctuating visibility ranging from good
to poor in short distances. If driving, slow down, use your low
beam headlights, and leave plenty of distance ahead of you.</description>
